</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2E605604FFCDFF9A07CCFF26130E8D2D" blockId="16.[211,1172,168,327]" pageId="16" pageNumber="1553">
<taxonomicName id="E9DF2D87FFCDFF9A07CCFF2613BF8C8D" authorityName="Dankittipakul &amp; Tavano &amp; Singtripop" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="Deeleman-Reinhold" baseAuthorityYear="2001" box="[211,386,208,231]" class="Arachnida" family="Liocranidae" genus="Jacaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="1553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erawan" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="1CAB8A16FFCDFF9A07CCFF2613BF8C8D" box="[211,386,208,231]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="1553">Jacaena erawan</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="0798376DFFCDFF9A0696FF3910388C8D" box="[393,517,207,231]" pageId="16" pageNumber="1553" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be easily distinguished by the truncated dRTA of the male palp when viewed from the ventral side (
<figureCitation id="B6E44A81FFCDFF9A05EAFF19114D8D6D" box="[757,880,239,263]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="11.[143,210,1565,1587]" captionTargetBox="[145,1102,161,1532]" captionTargetId="figure-5@11.[145,1102,161,1532]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 5. Jacaena spp. Male palps, ventral (A, D, G). Ditto, prolateral (B, E, H). Ditto, retrolateral (C, F, I). Jacaena erawan comb. nov., holotype (A–C); J. punctata sp. nov., holotype (D–F); J. thakek comb. nov., holotype (G–I)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6517654" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6517654/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="1553">Figure 5A</figureCitation>
), and by the base of the conductor that is rather broad and gradually tapered towards its apex (
<figureCitation id="B6E44A81FFCDFF9A0314FEF916B28D4D" box="[1035,1167,271,295]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="11.[143,210,1565,1587]" captionTargetBox="[145,1102,161,1532]" captionTargetId="figure-5@11.[145,1102,161,1532]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 5. Jacaena spp. Male palps, ventral (A, D, G). Ditto, prolateral (B, E, H). Ditto, retrolateral (C, F, I). Jacaena erawan comb. nov., holotype (A–C); J. punctata sp. nov., holotype (D–F); J. thakek comb. nov., holotype (G–I)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6517654" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6517654/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="1553">Figures 5A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="B6E44A81FFCDFF9A07CCFED9131A8D2D" box="[211,295,303,327]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="19.[143,210,929,951]" captionTargetBox="[145,1102,167,893]" captionTargetId="figure-5@19.[145,1102,167,896]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figure 11. Jacaena erawan comb. nov., holotype. Male palp, ventral (A). Ditto, prolateral (B). Anterior part of bulb, ventral (C). Palpal tibia, retrolateral (D)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6517672" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6517672/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="1553">11A–C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
